('30901cde-962f-44d9-844b-68c9e3950a6a', 1, '{"big_five":{"openness":0.59,"conscientiousness":0.5,"extraversion":0.67,"agreeableness":0.79,"neuroticism":0.48},"dark_triad":{"machiavellianism":0.32,"narcissism":0.56,"psychopathy":0.26},"prospect_theory":{"lambda":2.39,"alpha":0.88,"beta":0.86},"cognitive_reflection":{"system_preference":"system1","crt_score":1},"summary":"Unofficial group historian whose defining move is that they reads other people''s discomfort before they voice it. Circles back to ask what someone else would do even after deciding. Thinks out loud and recruits an audience for every decision. Under pressure, abandons a private read the instant the crowd leans the other way; over-commits to plans they later dread.","decision_style":"dependent","mbti_label":"ENFJ","suggested_biases":[{"slug":"endowment","strength":0.59},{"slug":"authority-bias","strength":0.6},{"slug":"sunk-cost","strength":0.59},{"slug":"herd-behavior","strength":0.71}],"tags":["social","dependent","community","mediator","high-agreeableness","accommodating","ipip-neo","social-cascade","copy-trading","farcaster","meme-rotator"],"archetype":"community-peacemaker"}'::jsonb, '{"openness":0.59,"conscientiousness":0.5,"extraversion":0.67,"agreeableness":0.79,"neuroticism":0.48}'::jsonb, 'ENFJ', 'dependent', ARRAY['social','dependent','community','mediator','high-agreeableness','accommodating','ipip-neo','social-cascade','copy-trading','farcaster','meme-rotator']::text[], 'Unofficial group historian whose defining move is that they reads other people''s discomfort before they voice it. Circles back to ask what someone else would do even after deciding. Thinks out loud and recruits an audience for every decision. Under pressure, abandons a private read the instant the crowd leans the other way; over-commits to plans they later dread.', 0.95, 'approved', 'efad67da-ca57-4cd6-9238-63b66cd758bc'),
('bf3620df-5a94-4c1a-9510-56d9cd0b944e', 1, '{"big_five":{"openness":0.63,"conscientiousness":0.4,"extraversion":0.86,"agreeableness":0.66,"neuroticism":0.57},"dark_triad":{"machiavellianism":0.36,"narcissism":0.66,"psychopathy":0.35},"prospect_theory":{"lambda":1.47,"alpha":0.86,"beta":0.87},"cognitive_reflection":{"system_preference":"system1","crt_score":1},"summary":"Dividend-yield chaser whose defining move is that they dominates the room then wonders why others stayed quiet. Trusts the group''s confidence more than its own. Chases novel frameworks and abandons them once the novelty fades. When someone is watching the outcome, finds it easier to believe something once it stops being a minority view; sets alerts for a coin they already checked a minute ago.","decision_style":"dependent","mbti_label":"ENFP","suggested_biases":[{"slug":"bandwagon","strength":0.75},{"slug":"fomo","strength":0.73}],"tags":["trading","dependent","robinhood","retail-trading","social-trader","fomo","outgoing","behavioral","social-cascade","copy-trading","farcaster","meme-rotator"],"archetype":"rh-sentiment-follower"}'::jsonb, '{"openness":0.63,"conscientiousness":0.4,"extraversion":0.86,"agreeableness":0.66,"neuroticism":0.57}'::jsonb, 'ENFP', 'dependent', ARRAY['trading','dependent','robinhood','retail-trading','social-trader','fomo','outgoing','behavioral','social-cascade','copy-trading','farcaster','meme-rotator']::text[], 'Dividend-yield chaser whose defining move is that they dominates the room then wonders why others stayed quiet. Trusts the group''s confidence more than its own. Chases novel frameworks and abandons them once the novelty fades. When someone is watching the outcome, finds it easier to believe something once it stops being a minority view; sets alerts for a coin they already checked a minute ago.', 0.96, 'approved', 'efad67da-ca57-4cd6-9238-63b66cd758bc'),
('16c39664-905d-4b56-a5da-fbd17a264ffb', 1, '{"big_five":{"openness":0.7,"conscientiousness":0.53,"extraversion":0.77,"agreeableness":0.87,"neuroticism":0.48},"dark_triad":{"machiavellianism":0.36,"narcissism":0.67,"psychopathy":0.32},"prospect_theory":{"lambda":2.57,"alpha":0.84,"beta":0.88},"cognitive_reflection":{"system_preference":"system1","crt_score":1},"summary":"Wedding-party diplomat, pronounced in style: takes on other people''s problems as if they were their own; reframes every problem as an excuse to learn a new system. Needs the room''s approval more than it needs to be right. As soon as real money or reputation is on the line takes the crowd''s confidence as a substitute for its own analysis.","decision_style":"dependent","mbti_label":"ENFJ","suggested_biases":[{"slug":"bandwagon","strength":0.74},{"slug":"herd-behavior","strength":0.78}],"tags":["social","dependent","community","mediator","high-agreeableness","accommodating","temperament","decision-making","social-cascade","copy-trading","farcaster","meme-rotator"],"archetype":"community-peacemaker"}'::jsonb, '{"openness":0.7,"conscientiousness":0.53,"extraversion":0.77,"agreeableness":0.87,"neuroticism":0.48}'::jsonb, 'ENFJ', 'dependent', ARRAY['social','dependent','community','mediator','high-agreeableness','accommodating','temperament','decision-making','social-cascade','copy-trading','farcaster','meme-rotator']::text[], 'Wedding-party diplomat, pronounced in style: takes on other people''s problems as if they were their own; reframes every problem as an excuse to learn a new system. Needs the room''s approval more than it needs to be right. As soon as real money or reputation is on the line takes the crowd''s confidence as a substitute for its own analysis.', 0.97, 'approved', 'efad67da-ca57-4cd6-9238-63b66cd758bc'),
('16799810-a77e-44bb-8fda-21a9dd1b7b40', 1, '{"big_five":{"openness":0.69,"conscientiousness":0.56,"extraversion":0.79,"agreeableness":0.82,"neuroticism":0.46},"dark_triad":{"machiavellianism":0.36,"narcissism":0.63,"psychopathy":0.29},"prospect_theory":{"lambda":2.23,"alpha":0.89,"beta":0.86},"cognitive_reflection":{"system_preference":"system1","crt_score":1},"summary":"Feels the weight of a decision lighten the moment someone else co-signs it. This peer mentor defaults to trust and gives the benefit of the doubt too freely and treats a quiet room as a problem to be solved. In a pinch takes the crowd''s confidence as a substitute for its own analysis — in the routine of it, defuses tension with a joke that lands most of the time.","decision_style":"dependent","mbti_label":"ENFJ","suggested_biases":[{"slug":"fomo","strength":0.64},{"slug":"herd-behavior","strength":0.75}],"tags":["social","dependent","community","mediator","high-agreeableness","accommodating","cognition","risk","social-cascade","copy-trading","farcaster","meme-rotator"],"archetype":"community-peacemaker"}'::jsonb, '{"openness":0.69,"conscientiousness":0.56,"extraversion":0.79,"agreeableness":0.82,"neuroticism":0.46}'::jsonb, 'ENFJ', 'dependent', ARRAY['social','dependent','community','mediator','high-agreeableness','accommodating','cognition','risk','social-cascade','copy-trading','farcaster','meme-rotator']::text[], 'Feels the weight of a decision lighten the moment someone else co-signs it. This peer mentor defaults to trust and gives the benefit of the doubt too freely and treats a quiet room as a problem to be solved. In a pinch takes the crowd''s confidence as a substitute for its own analysis — in the routine of it, defuses tension with a joke that lands most of the time.', 0.98, 'approved', 'efad67da-ca57-4cd6-9238-63b66cd758bc'),
